# MainForm and WinForms structure

## Where to edit (single source of truth)

- **`MainForm.cs`** — Constructor, shared fields, services wiring, shell (`BuildUi`, sidebar, tab host), tabs except POS, reports, and main warehouse (`BuildInventoryTab`, catalog, branches, transfers, audit), data-load orchestration (`LoadDataAsync`, warehouses, stock refresh), and shared helpers not owned by another partial.
- **`MainForm.MainWarehouse.cs`** — Main warehouse tab (`BuildMainWarehouseTab`), grid/pager, Excel import/export, purchase CRUD, branch price overrides, `MainWarehouseCatalogRow` / `MainWarehouseRow`, `ReadCommittedNumericUpDown`, `SelectMainWarehouseComboValue`, `RestoreMainWarehouseFieldCaptionFonts`, and related helpers.
- **`MainForm.Reports.cs`** — Reports / analytics tab (`BuildReportsTab`), all `Configure*Report*` grid columns, `ApplyReportsVisualStyle`, `RefreshReportsAsync`, report stock history helpers, expense save from reports, `ExportAnalyticsReportsToExcelAsync`.
- **`MainForm.Pos.cs`** — POS tab (`BuildPosTab`), cart/sale/oil-change flows, product cards, category chips, POS warehouse/customer resolution, `AvailableProductRow` / `CartRow`, product image map JSON for POS cards.
- **`MainForm.UiPrimitives.cs`** — Reusable static UI: `BuildCard`, `BuildTwoColRow`, `StyleGrid`, `StyleReportGrid`, `BuildAnalyticsKpiCard`, `CreateReportPillButton`, `BuildSizedButton`, etc.

Before adding or changing a method, **search all `MainForm*.cs` partials** for an existing definition (`BuildPosTab`, `RefreshReportsAsync`, `StyleGrid`, …). **Never duplicate** the same member in two partials (causes CS0111).

## WinForms resources

- Only **`MainForm.resx`** may exist for this type. Do **not** add `MainForm.<Something>.resx` for partials (MSB3577 duplicate `MainForm.resources`).

## SOLID (practical for this codebase)

- **SRP** — Keep POS in `MainForm.Pos.cs`, reports in `MainForm.Reports.cs`, main warehouse in `MainForm.MainWarehouse.cs`, shared visual building blocks in `MainForm.UiPrimitives.cs`, and cross-tab orchestration in `MainForm.cs`. Prefer small private methods with one clear job.
- **DIP** — Use `ISalesService`, `IInventoryService`, `IReportService`, etc. from `OilChangePOS.Business`; avoid embedding data access or business rules in the form beyond UI glue.
- **Open/closed** — Extend via new private methods in the relevant partial or new service methods in Business, rather than growing one giant method when avoidable.

## Token-efficient workflow for AI edits

1. State the feature (e.g. “POS cart column”, “report grid columns”).
2. Open **only** the partial that owns that area (see above).
3. If a change touches services or DTOs, open the matching **`OilChangePOS.Business`** (or Domain/Data) file — not the whole solution.

## Optional future refactors (when you have time)

- Extract nested row/DTO types (`InventoryRow`, audit rows, etc.) into `OilChangePOS.WinForms/Models/` or `.../ViewModels/` to shrink `MainForm.cs` and improve reuse/testing.
- Extract “refresh all stock views” / warehouse combo sync into a small dedicated type (e.g. `StockViewSynchronizer`) injected or created from `MainForm` — reduces form size without changing behavior.
